The paper also discusses the importance of scale normalization, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Furthermore, the paper makes a connection between sharpness and PAC-Bayes theory, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper investigates different observed phenomena, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
